     1	# Gold Standard — Backward-Facing Step
     2	# Primary anchor: Le, Moin & Kim 1997, J. Fluid Mech. 330, 349-374 (DNS).
     3	# Corroborating: Armaly et al. 1983, J. Fluid Mech. 127, 473-496 (experiment).
     4	#
     5	# Anchor choice (Gate Q-4 Path A closure, 2026-04-21):
     6	#   The whitelist runs this case at Re_H=7600 (bulk-velocity/step-height
     7	#   Reynolds number). In that regime Le/Moin/Kim's Re_H=5100 DNS gives
     8	#   Xr/H = 6.28 — nearest-regime literature value. The earlier anchor
     9	#   (Driver & Seegmiller 1985 Re_H≈36000 fully-turbulent experiment,
    10	#   Xr/H=6.26) was dropped because it cited turbulent-regime data for a
    11	#   transitional-regime run. Numerically similar (~6.2) but not
    12	#   physically congruent.
    13	# Expansion ratio 1.125, incompressible, steady.
    14	# INTERNAL flow over a backward-facing step.
