    17	  geometry_assumption: "Backward-facing step, step height H=1, channel_height=1.125·H (expansion ratio 1.125), 2D with empty front/back (SIMPLE_GRID adapter path); upstream/downstream channel lengths per whitelist defaults."
    18	  reference_correlation_context: "Le, Moin & Kim 1997 DNS at Re_H=5100 reports Xr/H=6.28 for a BFS with expansion ratio 1.2 (closest published DNS to our regime). Our whitelist runs at Re_H=7600, which sits in the post-transition regime where Xr/H is weakly Re-sensitive relative to the declared 10% tolerance (literature shows Xr/H saturating above Re≈5000 into a slow plateau; the exact 5100→7600 drift is not a tight 2% number and depends on expansion ratio, inlet BL state, and 2D/3D effects). Gate Q-4 Path A closure (DEC-V61-028, 2026-04-21) switched the anchor from Driver & Seegmiller 1985 Re_H≈36000 (turbulent experiment) to Le/Moin/Kim 5100 DNS for closer-regime match."
