     1	# cfd-harness-unified
     2	
     3	A demo-first AI-CFD workbench. Ten canonical flow problems, each paired with
     4	its historical gold standard, tolerance band, and common pitfalls — so you can
     5	see the distance between *getting a number* and *getting it right*.
     6	
     7	## Quick start
     8	
     9	```bash
    10	# Python 3.12 is the supported runtime. Everything below assumes .venv is
    11	# Python 3.12.x (see `./.venv/bin/python --version`).
    12	python3.12 -m venv .venv
    13	.venv/bin/pip install -e ".[ui,dev]"
    14	(cd ui/frontend && npm install)
    15	
    16	./scripts/start-ui-dev.sh
    17	# UI:      http://127.0.0.1:5180/learn          ← demo front door
    18	# Pro:     http://127.0.0.1:5180/pro            ← evidence workbench
    19	# API doc: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/docs
    20	```
    21	
    22	## What you see
    23	
    24	### `/learn` — demo front door
    25	
    26	Ten classic CFD problems as a visual catalog. Each card carries its historical
    27	citation, a difficulty dot, and a one-line teaser. Click into a case and you
    28	get five tabs:
    29	
    30	- **故事 / Story** — physics, canonical reference, why validation matters, the
    31	  literature reference plot, and the solver contour + residuals from a real
    32	  OpenFOAM run.
    33	- **对比 / Compare** — your measurement vs. the gold value on a tolerance band.
    34	  Run selector lets you flip between reference / under-resolved / wrong-model
    35	  runs to watch the verdict change — that's the teaching moment.
    36	- **网格 / Mesh** — grid-convergence slider (4 densities), live sparkline that
    37	  plots your measurement as it converges toward gold.
    38	- **运行 / Run** — jump into Pro Workbench for the real solver loop.
    39	- **进阶 / Advanced** — decision trail, audit concerns, signed audit package
    40	  builder.
    41	
    42	Anchor cases (the ones with the tightest story → compare → evidence loop):
    43	
    44	- `lid_driven_cavity` (Ghia 1982)
    45	- `circular_cylinder_wake` (Williamson 1996)
    46	- `naca0012_airfoil` (Ladson 1988)
    47	
    48	### `/pro` — evidence workbench
    49	
    50	Path B V&V-first surface for audit, regulated-industry contexts, and anyone
    51	who needs to hand a CFD result to someone whose signature is on the line.
    52	Screens: Dashboard · Cases · Decisions · Runs · Audit Package.
    53	
    54	Not the right starting point for a demo. Reachable from every `/learn` page
    55	via `进入专业工作台 →` and from the top-nav `Pro Workbench →` link.
    56	
    57	## Testing
    58	
    59	```bash
    60	# Core engine + knowledge + report engine
    61	.venv/bin/pytest
    62	
    63	# UI backend (FastAPI routes, comparator gates, attestor, audit package)
    64	.venv/bin/pytest ui/backend/tests -q
    65	
    66	# UI frontend
    67	(cd ui/frontend && npm run typecheck && npm run build)
    68	```
    69	
    70	## Architecture (one screen)
    71	
    72	```
    73	knowledge/whitelist.yaml + knowledge/gold_standards/*.yaml
    74	       │
    75	       ├─► auto_verifier  ─────► report_engine  ─────► reports/<case>/
    76	       │                                                auto_verify_report.yaml
    77	       │
    78	       ├─► task_runner  ──► FoamAgentExecutor ──► reports/phase5_fields/<case>/
