duct_flow => SATISFIED | SATISFIED — all three physics preconditions met. Prior `fully_developed_pipe` contract_status was `INCOMPATIBLE` (precondition #1 unmet) because the adapter produced a duct but the label said pipe. Rename resolves the inconsistency. Any comparator deviation is now a genuine solver / mesh / turbulence-model convergence question, not a regime mismatch.

