The consolidated verdict in that file is `BLOCK`. The two highest-signal blockers are: `partial` physics preconditions are still being coerced to `true` in the live `/pro` API/UI path, and the current tree does not reproduce the claimed green state for the review-relevant subset. I reran `ui/backend/tests/test_case_export.py ui/backend/tests/test_decisions_and_dashboard.py tests/test_report_engine/test_contract_dashboard_report.py` on April 22, 2026 and got `26 passed, 1 failed`; the failing assertion is `test_contract_dashboard_generate_writes_output`, where the manifest no longer matches the pinned distribution. The file also calls out the main demo/business issue that `/learn` still reads as a Chinese teaching catalog before it reads as a buyer-facing AI-CFD workbench, plus the CFD-specific issues around the BFS anchor inconsistency and over-claimed `<2%` plateau language.

Primary literature used for the CFD judgments:
- Ghia, Ghia & Shin 1982 cavity benchmark PDF: https://www.ljll.fr/~frey/papers/Navier-Stokes/Ghia%20V.%2C%20High-Resolutions%20for%20incompressible%20flow%20using%20the%20Navier-Stokes%20equations%20and%20a%20multi-grid%20method.pdf
- Le, Moin & Kim 1997 BFS DNS abstract: https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/journal-of-fluid-mechanics/article/abs/direct-numerical-simulation-of-turbulent-flow-over-a-backwardfacing-step/645D21758E8F74568008899C17B12ADD
- Armaly et al. 1983 BFS experiment PDF: https://courses.washington.edu/me431/handouts/armaly-jfm-83.pdf
- Kim, Moin & Moser 1987 channel-flow paper PDF: https://chaosbook.org/library/KimJFM87.pdf
- Baughn & Shimizu 1989 impinging-jet paper record: https://www.osti.gov/biblio/6064124
- Akiyama et al. 2005 planar impinging jets abstract: https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0142727X04001316


